---
import BaseLayout from '../../components/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
    title="Texas Momentum & Market Dominance | TomorrowBeginsHere.com"
    description="Learn why Texas is winning the digital infrastructure expansion, employing 10% of the national workforce and capturing billions in capital investments."
>
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div class="bg-slate-900 border-b border-tech-blue/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-950/80 via-slate-900/95 to-tech-blue/80 z-0 mix-blend-multiply"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/texas-data-centers-network.png')] bg-cover bg-center z-0 opacity-15 mix-blend-overlay"></div>
        <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20 lg:py-24 text-center">
            <span class="inline-block px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full bg-teal-500/20 text-teal-300 font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-sm mb-6 border border-teal-500/30 backdrop-blur-sm">Pillar 02 • Market Momentum</span>
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6 tracking-tight leading-tight">
                Texas is Already Winning:<br><span class="text-teal-300">Momentum is Its Own Argument</span>
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-200 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed font-light">
                Digital infrastructure capital is moving rapidly. Texas has established itself as the premier national destination, and the communities that act now will lock in generational tax benefits.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white relative">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none">
                
                <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-700 font-medium">
                    Investors and operators prefer to deploy capital in states with proven success. Texas has developed a highly specialized supply chain, a skilled technical workforce, and a clear regulatory pathway that has propelled the state to the forefront of the global infrastructure race.
                </p>

                <!-- Stats Grid -->
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-12">
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
                        <div class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-tech-blue mb-1">47,856+</div>
                        <div class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Direct Texas Jobs</div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-0">
                            Texas employs approximately 10% of the entire national data center operations workforce.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
                        <div class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-tech-blue mb-1">+38%</div>
                        <div class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Workforce Growth</div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-0">
                            Data center employment in Texas expanded by 38% between 2018 and 2024.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
                        <div class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-tech-blue mb-1">2nd Largest</div>
                        <div class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">North American Market</div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-0">
                            Dallas-Fort Worth has grown to become the second-largest data center market in North America.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
                        <div class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-tech-blue mb-1">$3 Trillion</div>
                        <div class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Projected National Spend</div>
                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-0">
                            Industry projections forecast up to $500 billion spent in 2026, reaching $3 trillion by 2028.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-6">The Cost of Hesitation</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    A massive, multi-trillion-dollar capital wave is currently being deployed to build out global compute capacity. These investments represent long-term, tangible infrastructure: fiber optic grids, electrical substations, cooling facilities, and physical buildings that will generate commercial property taxes for 30+ years.
                </p>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    This capital does not wait for municipal hesitation. If a county delays planning or blocks a clean facility, operators do not cancel their projects. They simply route their fiber and capital to the neighboring county. The neighbor captures the tax base and builds new school facilities, while the hesitating community watches the opportunity pass by.
                </p>

                <!-- Informational quote banner -->
                <div class="bg-teal-50/60 border border-teal-100 rounded-3xl p-8 my-12 text-center">
                    <p class="text-xl italic font-semibold text-teal-900 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        "The wave of digital infrastructure is active now. Texas is leading this expansion. The choice for our local communities is simple: capture the tax base today, or let it land next door."
                    </p>
                    <span class="text-sm font-bold text-teal-800 uppercase tracking-widest">— Texas Economic Development Council</span>
                </div>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-6">A Magnet for Prosperity</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    Joining a winning market means local businesses benefit from a robust ecosystem. When operators choose Texas, they bring tier-1 engineering partners, equipment suppliers, and utility financing. This creates a dense network of high-paying local careers and business contracts, reinforcing the state's economic resilience.
                </p>

                <hr class="border-slate-200 my-12">

                <div class="text-center bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-3xl p-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                    <p class="text-slate-500 mb-4 uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-bold">Explore the next pillar</p>
                    <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Pillar 03: The Local Closer — Funding Public Services</h4>
                    <a href="/texas-data-centers/tax-closer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-6 py-3 bg-tech-blue hover:bg-tech-blue/90 text-white font-bold rounded-xl transition-colors">
                        Next: Local Tax Impact
                        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
                        </svg>
                    </a>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
